---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="Security Solution Provisioning — Toss Insurance"
  description="Slack Bot self-service automation for security solution provisioning."
  pathname="/projects/toss"
>
  <article class="container-prose pt-20 pb-16">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
      Project 3 · Jan 2025 – May 2025
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold mb-4" style="line-height: 1.2;">
      Security Solution Provisioning Automation
    </h1>
    <p class="text-base mb-8" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
      IT Supporter @ Toss Insurance · Python, Slack Bot API, Microsoft 365 Admin
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">The Problem</h2>
    <p>
      Toss Insurance's IT team handled a high volume of repetitive help desk requests for
      security solution provisioning — granting access, configuring endpoint protection, managing
      user lifecycle across multiple security platforms. Each request required manual steps
      across several admin consoles.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">The Solution</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">A Python-based automation system integrated with Slack Bot:</p>
    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
      <li>Receives provisioning requests through a Slack interface</li>
      <li>Automatically provisions users across security solution platforms</li>
      <li>Confirms completion back to the requester via Slack</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="mt-4">
      Additional supporting work included Windows / macOS support, Microsoft 365 user lifecycle
      and licensing, Google Workspace 2FA exception management, IP exhaustion / subnet
      diagnostics, malware detection accuracy validation, and Hypervisor-based isolated
      environments for public-institution software conflicts.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">Results</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
      <li><strong>70% reduction</strong> in help desk inquiries</li>
      <li>Provisioning time: manual multi-step → automated single trigger</li>
      <li>Error rate: human-dependent → near zero (scripted)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">What I Learned</h2>
    <p>
      The biggest impact came not from the automation itself, but from the Slack Bot interface.
      By making the system self-service, users stopped filing help desk tickets entirely. The
      lesson: <strong
        >the best automation is the one users don't even think of as automation.</strong
      >
    </p>

    <p class="mt-8 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
      <em>Source code is held under prior employer's confidentiality.</em>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
